<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
	<head>
		<meta charset="UTF-8">
		<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
		<title>Web Development Milestones</title>
		<style>
			body {
				font-family: 'Arial', sans-serif;
				margin: 0;
				padding: 0;
				background-color: #f4f4f4;
			}
			header {
				background-color: #2F4F4F;
				color: #fff;
				text-align: center;
				padding: 20px 0;
			}
			header h1 {
				margin: 0;
				font-size: 2.5em;
			}
			section {
				max-width: 1000px;
				margin: 20px auto;
				background-color: #fff;
				padding: 20px;
				border-radius: 8px;
				box-shadow: 0 0 10px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
			}
			section h2 {
				color: #4682B4;
				border-bottom: 2px solid #2F4F4F;
				padding-bottom: 10px;
			}
			ul {
				list-style-type: none;
				padding: 0;
			}
			li {
				margin-bottom: 10px;
				padding: 10px;
				background-color: #e7f1ff;
				border-left: 5px solid #4682B4;
			}
			span {
				font-weight: bold;
			}
			@media(max-width: 600px) {
				header h1 {
					font-size: 2em;
				}
			}
		</style>
	</head>
	<body>
		<header>
			<h1>Key Milestones in Web Development</h1>
		</header>
		<section>
			<h2>1990s - Birth of the Web</h2>
			<ul>
				<li>
					<span>1990:</span>
					Tim Berners-Lee invented the World Wide Web.</li>
				<li>
					<span>1993:</span>
					Mosaic, the first widely used web browser, was introduced.</li>
				<li>
					<span>1995:</span>
					Introduction of JavaScript by Netscape.</li>
				<li>
					<span>1998:</span>
					Google was founded, changing the way we search the internet.</li>
			</ul>
			<h2>2000s - Web 2.0 and the Rise of Social Media</h2>
			<ul>
				<li>
					<span>2001:</span>
					Launch of Wikipedia.</li>
				<li>
					<span>2004:</span>
					Facebook was launched.</li>
				<li>
					<span>2005:</span>
					YouTube was launched.</li>
				<li>
					<span>2006:</span>
					jQuery was released, simplifying JavaScript programming.</li>
			</ul>
			<h2>2010s - Mobile and Responsive Design</h2>
			<ul>
				<li>
					<span>2010:</span>
					HTML5 was released, adding new features for web developers.</li>
				<li>
					<span>2011:</span>
					Introduction of Bootstrap, aiding in responsive web design.</li>
				<li>
					<span>2014:</span>
					Google introduced Material Design.</li>
			</ul>
			<h2>2020s - Modern Web Development</h2>
			<ul>
				<li>
					<span>2020:</span>
					Launch of Next.js, enhancing server-side rendering and static site generation.</li>
				<li>
					<span>2021:</span>
					Popularity of WebAssembly, enabling high-performance applications in web browsers.</li>
				<li>
					<span>2022:</span>
					Introduction of new JavaScript frameworks like SvelteKit and Qwik.</li>
				<li>
					<span>2023:</span>
					Continued growth of Progressive Web Apps (PWAs).</li>
			</ul>
		</section>
	</body>
</html>
